    <!-- Waterfalls Section -->
    <section class="waterfalls-section" id="waterfalls">
        <div class="tours-section-header">
            <h2>💧 Beautiful waterfalls in Umphang</h2>
            <p>Explore 6 WaterfallkmMagnificent of umphang DistrictCliffง</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Waterfalls Grid Container -->
        <div class="waterfalls-container">

        <!-- Thailosu Waterfall Info -->
        <div class="thailosu-info-section">
            <div class="info-card main">
                <div class="thailosu-hero-image waterfall-preview" onclick="openLightbox('thailosu-main.jpg', 'Thi Lo Su Waterfall')">
                    <img src="thailosu-main.jpg" alt="Thi Lo Su Waterfall" onerror="this.src='https://via.placeholder.com/1200x600/E5E7EB/1A1A1A?text=Thailosu+Waterfall';">
                </div>
                <h3>💧 Thi Lo Su Waterfall</h3>
                <p class="highlight">The most beautiful limestone waterfall in Thailand</p>
                <div class="info-grid">
                    <div class="info-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-mountain"></i>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Height</strong>
                            <span>300 Meters</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-ruler-horizontal"></i>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Width</strong>
                            <span>Approximately 500 Meters</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Location</strong>
                            <span>Umphang Wildlife Sanctuary, Tak Province</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-water"></i>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Water source</strong>
                            <span>Huay Klot Tho Stream</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="description">Waterfall flows through steep cliffs in tiers, creating thunderous sounds amidst lush tropical forest</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Nearby Attractions -->
            <div class="info-cards-row">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <h4>🗺️ Nearby Attractions</h4>
                    <ul class="attractions-list">
                        <li><strong>Thi Lo Jo Waterfall</strong> - Limestone waterfall flowing from stream to river</li>
                        <li><strong>Rainbow Waterfall</strong> Must visit by boat. See rainbows from water spray</li>
                        <li><strong>Pa Charoen Waterfall</strong> 97-tier waterfall</li>
                        <li><strong>Thi Lo Le Waterfall</strong> In upper forest area of Mae Klong River</li>
                        <li><strong>Doi Hua Mot</strong> Sea of mist viewpoint</li>
                        <li><strong>Takoe Bi Cave</strong> Large cave</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <h4>🎯 Tourist Activities</h4>
                    <ul class="activities-list">
                        <li>🚣 Rubber boat rafting to waterfall (formerly raft)</li>
                        <li>🦇 Cave exploration</li>
                        <li>🌅 Sea of mist viewing</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Important Info -->
            <div class="info-cards-row">
                <div class="info-card warning">
                    <h4>⚠️ Important Notices</h4>
                    <p><strong>Rainy season:</strong> Is when the waterfall is most beautiful. However, Umphang Wildlife Sanctuary closes vehicle routes due to difficult access and for forest conservation.</p>
                    <p><strong>Travel during rainy season:</strong> Must contact local tour company in the area. Has 2 routes:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>🚣 Rubber boat from Tha Sai, Umphang → Mae Klong River (3 hrs) + Trekking (10 km, 3 hrs)</li>
                        <li>🚶 Trekking from Huai Nong Luang Ranger Station → Thi Lo Su Waterfall (25 km, 4-5 hrs)</li>
                    </ol>
                    <p class="warning-text">⚠️ Must obtain permission from Umphang Wildlife Sanctuary officials before every visit</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card success">
                    <h4>🚗 Travel Information</h4>
                    <p><strong>Route:</strong> Umphang District-Mae KlongNew MaeAnd → km to 20 Turn left → Sanctuary Umphang District (26 km.)</p>
                    <p class="warning-text">⚠️ Off-road track. Pickup truck or 4WD vehicle required only</p>
                    <p><strong>Rainy season:</strong> Vehicles may not access. Recommend contacting local tour companies in Umphang District, which usually include Thi Lo Su Waterfall tours in their programs already.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Pitue Gro Waterfall Section -->
        <div class="pituegro-info-section">
            <div class="info-card main pituegro">
                <div class="pituegro-hero-image waterfall-preview" onclick="openLightbox('pituegro-main.jpg', 'Pitue Gro Waterfall - Heart-shaped waterfall')">
                    <img src="pituegro-main.jpg" alt="Pitue Gro Waterfall" onerror="this.src='https://via.placeholder.com/1200x600/E5E7EB/1A1A1A?text=Pitue+Gro+Waterfall';">
                </div>
                <h3>💕 Pitue Gro Waterfall - Heart-shaped waterfall of Western Forest</h3>
                <p class="highlight">Waterfall over 500 meters high with clear heart shape</p>

                <div class="info-grid">
                    <div class="info-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-heart"></i>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Characteristics</strong>
                            <span>Heart shape (water flows in two streams)</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-ruler-vertical"></i>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Height</strong>
                            <span>Over 500 meters</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Location</strong>
                            <span>Umphang District, Tak Province</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-tree"></i>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Area</strong>
                            <span>Western Forest Complex</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <p class="description">This waterfall, towering over 500 meters in height, is distinguished by its remarkable formation. Two powerful streams cascade down along separate sides before gracefully converging at the base, creating a striking and unmistakable heart shape.</p>

                <div class="adventure-badge">
                    <i class="fas fa-heart"></i>
                    <span>The most beautiful heart-shaped waterfall in Thailand</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Travel Info -->
            <div class="info-card warning">
                <h4>🥾 Travel to Pitue Gro Waterfall</h4>

                <div class="travel-steps">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon">🚶</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <strong>Route</strong>
                            <span>Through lowland villages + Water crossing, muddy trek</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon">⚠️</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <strong>Steep trail</strong>
                            <span>Along the trail to waterfall (Water crossing, cliff edge, climbing)</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon">👟</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <strong>Recommendation</strong>
                            <span>Recommendation: Wear non-slip shoes for your safety</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <p class="warning-text">⚠️ Along the way you will cross water, trek through mud, and climb in some sections. Recommend bringing non-slip shoes</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Adventure Review Section -->
            <div class="info-card adventure-review">
                <div class="adventure-review-image">
                    <img src="doi-mamuang-main.jpg" alt="Doi Mamuang Sam Muen Summit" onerror="this.src='https://via.placeholder.com/1200x600/E5E7EB/1A1A1A?text=Doi+Mamuang+Sam+Muen';">
                </div>
                <h4>🎒 Tourist Review: So fun, its worth it!!</h4>

                <div class="review-highlight">
                    <p class="highlight-text">"Fun riding, water trekking, ridge walking - so fun its worth it! …"</p>
                </div>

                <p class="review-text">About trips with water crossing, mud trekking, ridge walking - everyone must have Pitue Gro on their list! I've read many reviews about conquering the trek to the waterfall. But for this one, approximately everyone will review about climbing <strong>Doi Mamuang Sam Muen Summit</strong> instead. Which is the highest point here. One word: exhaustingly amazing!</p>

                <div class="doi-mamuang-info">
                    <h5>🏔️ Doi Mamuang Sam Muen Summit</h5>
                    <div class="info-grid">
                        <div class="info-item">
                            <i class="fas fa-ruler-vertical"></i>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Height</strong>
                                <span>Approximately 1,600 meters</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="info-item">
                            <i class="fas fa-route"></i>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Distance</strong>
                                <span>Over 7 kilometers</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="info-item">
                            <i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Location</strong>
                                <span>Umphang District, Tak Province</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="info-item">
                            <i class="fas fa-tree"></i>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Area</strong>
                                <span>Western Forest Complex</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="trail-review">
                    <h5>🥾 Trail Review</h5>
                    <p>About 7 km but the trail is challenging ... The walking path has both flat and steep sections alternating</p>

                    <div class="trail-features">
                        <div class="trail-feature">
